y VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":70,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Issobell was born in 1385, in Moulton, Suffolk, England. She married Sir George Moodye. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died on 8 February 1467, in Suffolk, England, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1385–8 February 1467":"1385–8. veebruar 1467","1380–1430":"1380–1430","1400–1460":"1400–1460","1410–Male":"1410–Surnud","1385–1467":"1385–1467","1467":"1467","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1385":"1385","1460":"1460","8 February 1467":"8. veebruar 1467","1380":"1380","Norwich, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Harwich, Essex, England":"Harwich, Essex, England","Moulton, Suffolk, England":"Moulton, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1385–8 February 1467":"1385–8. helmikuuta 1467","1380–1430":"1380–1430","1400–1460":"1400–1460","1410–Male":"1410–Kuollut","1385–1467":"1385–1467","1467":"1467","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1385":"1385","1460":"1460","8 February 1467":"8. helmikuuta 1467","1380":"1380","Norwich, Su